"\n_____________________________________________________________\n"
"[3. For-In]"
"A For-In can be used to iterate every object of a List, Set or String."
"Consider the example:"
"text = \"Bern\""
"for char : text do"
"   \"Current char is:\" + char"
"end"

"\nResult:"

text = "Bern"
for char : text do
   "Current char is: " + char
end

"\n_____________________________________________________________\n"
"[3. For-In with Counter]"
"An automatic enumeration is also available with the following syntax:"
"Consider the example:"
"text = \"Bern\""
"for char, index : text do"
"   \"Current char is:\" + char"
"   \"Current index is:\" + index"
"end"

"\nResult:"

textt = "Bern"
for char, index : textt do
   "Current char is: " + char
    "Current index is: " + index
end